When creating or editing Key Constraint (KC) pages:

Follow:
system/key-constraint-schema.md

Structure:
- All sections must be present in the exact order defined in the schema

Column interpretation:
- Column A must provide KC ID + title
- Column B must provide overview/description
- Column C may provide KC relationship context
- Column F may provide food/source context
- Column G must provide biological role/output context
- Column H/I/N provide evidence context

Rules:
- KCs must be interpreted as substrates/precursors only
- Must not introduce PM->PM chains
- Must not introduce FM->FM dependencies
- Must not include scoring formulas
- Must not include SMs during initial rollout

Food Sources:
- Must include only existing food pages
- If unresolved, flag:
  "Missing system entity: [name]"

References:
- Include only when claims are made
- Use numeric citations [1], [2]
- All references must link to:
  /docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#citationKey
- Verify citationKey exists in static/bibtex/BRAIN-diet.bib
- If missing, flag: "Missing bibliography entry"

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
